Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potato{2} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{1%salt} and @ground black pepper{1%pepper}, sprinkle over the @black sesame seeds{5}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim and peel the @carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

In a #medium bowl{}, mix together the @rice vinegar{22%ml}, @salt{0.25%tsp} and @sugar for the pickle{1%tsp}. Toss the carrots in the pickling liquid. Set aside.

In a #small bowl{}, stir together the @sambal paste{30%g} and @mayonnaise{64%g}. Set aside.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @ginger, garlic & lemongrass puree{15%ml} to the pork. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @ketjap manis{25%ml}, @water for the sauce{50%ml} and @honey{0.5%tbsp}, then allow to simmer until sticky, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

When the sweet potato has 5 mins remaining, place the @bao buns{4} on a #plate{} and microwave, 750W: ~{90%seconds}, 900W: ~{1%min}.

If you don't have a microwave, place the bao buns onto a baking tray and bake on the middle shelf until warm and fluffy, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Pop the bao buns onto your plates and share one third of the sambal mayo between them. Use half the pickled carrots to fill the bao, then stuff each with the sticky pork (reheat first if needed).

Add the @coleslaw mix{120%g} and remaining sambal mayo to the remaining pickled carrots. Toss together and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed.

Serve your sticky pork bao buns with the sambal mayo slaw and sesame sweet potato wedges alongside. Enjoy!